Generation17 Young Leader Renata Koch Alvarenga has been fighting for climate justice—ensuring equitable climate solutions for nearly a decade. When catastrophic floods devastated her home state in Brazil in 2024, it was a painful reminder of what she already knew: climate disasters hit the most vulnerable communities, including women and girls, the hardest. Through her organization, EmpoderaClima, Renata is building a powerful network of underrepresented climate leaders—training them in everything from disaster preparedness to climate advocacy. Her mission? Ensuring youth and women lead the fight for our planet's future.
